     Now you've come to a point in the quest at which you will have
to engage in one of the most common activities of any quest:
exploration.  In order to find the goblin cave Ezekiel referred
to, you're going to have to look through the area, covering quite
a large portion of the place.  It is always a good idea to do this
while engaged in a quest and it is also a good to make a map while
doing so, both so that you won't become completely lost and
so that you might more easily move through the region.  A very
interesting consequence of exploring an area fully and making a
map as you go along is that you quite often can see where secret
passageways and such might be just by looking at the gaps in your
map!  Therefore, you should truly try to cover as much of a quest
area as you can, making a simple map, so as to ease your progress
through it.  While you are doing so, it is also good to remember
to examine what seem to be important features of every room
as these often provide clues about things which pop up during
the quest itself.  Now judging what is an important feature and
what isn't is not easy to do, and the ability to do so
really only comes with experience.  A safer approach is to examine
all the features of every room.  While this can be a bit tedious,
especially if the quest area is large, it is bound to yield
abundant information, especially if the quest is heavy on
thinking and exploration and not so much on combat.  Go looking
about this area now, being sure to cover the whole place, and
make a map while you do so, just for practice.
